trend_summary: Across the series, the suburb keeps its grid, but infill and commercial redevelopment slowly raise built-up cover. A widened freeway and new ramps appear south-east, while the diagonal retail corridor gains larger roofs and parking reconfiguration. Tree canopy thickens and small parks emerge, balancing moderate growth so density stays medium suburban.
notable_changes: Freeway at south-east widened and new interchange ramps added.
Larger commercial buildings replace older strip malls along the central diagonal corridor.
New institutional/office complex constructed near the north-east, visible by dark roof then completion.
Residential infill: vacant lots converted to townhouses and cul-de-sac extensions.
Tree canopy and landscaped green patches expand, creating additional small park areas.
